Here is the Terraform configuration for creating an `aws_connect_bot_association` resource.

This configuration includes the resource definition and the necessary variables. It utilizes the Amazon Lex V2 bot configuration, which is the current standard, though the resource also supports Lex V1.

```hcl
# Variable for the Amazon Connect Instance ID
variable "connect_instance_id" {
  description = "The identifier of the Amazon Connect instance."
  type        = string
}

# Variable for the Lex V2 Bot ID
variable "lex_bot_id" {
  description = "The identifier of the Amazon Lex V2 bot."
  type        = string
}

# Variable for the Lex V2 Bot Alias ID
variable "lex_bot_alias_id" {
  description = "The identifier of the Amazon Lex V2 bot alias."
  type        = string
}

# Variable for the Lex V2 Locale ID
variable "lex_bot_locale_id" {
  description = "The identifier of the Amazon Lex V2 bot locale (e.g., en_US)."
  type        = string
  default     = "en_US"
}

# Resource: Associates the Amazon Connect Instance with the Lex V2 Bot
resource "aws_connect_bot_association" "main" {
  instance_id = var.connect_instance_id

  lex_v2_bot {
    alias_id  = var.lex_bot_alias_id
    bot_id    = var.lex_bot_id
    locale_id = var.lex_bot_locale_id
  }
}
