Tofulfill this request, we need to create the `aws_sagemaker_user_profile` resource.

Here is the step-by-step plan:
1.  **Define the IAM Role**: A SageMaker User Profile requires an execution role to assume permissions for accessing data (S3) and other services. We will create an `aws_iam_role` with a trust relationship allowing `sagemaker.amazonaws.com` to assume it.
2.  **Attach Permissions**: We will attach the `AmazonSageMakerFullAccess` policy to this role so the user has the necessary permissions to perform tasks within Studio.
3.  **Define the User Profile**: We will create the `aws_sagemaker_user_profile` resource. This requires a `domain_id` (which we will define as a variable, assuming the domain exists) and a `user_profile_name`. We will link the IAM role created in step 1 within the `user_settings` block.

```hcl
# 1. Variable for the Domain ID
# The SageMaker User Profile must be associated with an existing Domain.
variable "domain_id" {
  description = "The ID of the SageMaker Domain to attach the user profile to"
  type        = string
}

# 2. IAM Execution Role
# The user profile needs an execution role to permissions to interact with AWS services.
resource "aws_iam_role" "sagemaker_execution_role" {
  name = "sagemaker-user-profile-execution-role"

  assume_role_policy = jsonencode({
    Version = "2012-10-17"
    Statement = [
      {
        Action = "sts:AssumeRole"
        Effect = "Allow"
        Principal = {
          Service = "sagemaker.amazonaws.com"
        }
      }
    ]
  })
}

# 3. Attach Policy to the Role
# Attaching a managed policy to provide necessary permissions for the user.
# In a production environment, you should scope this down to the least privilege required.
resource "aws_iam_role_policy_attachment" "sagemaker_execution_policy" {
  role       = aws_iam_role.sagemaker_execution_role.name
  policy_arn = "arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonSageMakerFullAccess"
}

# 4. SageMaker User Profile Resource
# This creates the actual user profile within the specified Domain.
resource "aws_sagemaker_user_profile" "example" {
  domain_id         = var.domain_id
  user_profile_name = "example-user-profile"

  user_settings {
    execution_role = aws_iam_role.sagemaker_execution_role.arn

    # Optional: Define default settings for the Jupyter Server App
    jupyter_server_app_settings {
      default_resource_spec {
        instance_type = "ml.t3.medium"
        lifecycle_config_arn = ""
        sagemaker_image_arn = ""
      }
    }
  }

  tags = {
    Environment = "Production"
    ManagedBy   = "Terraform"
  }
}
```

