response:
To enable Point-in-Time Recovery (PITR) for a DynamoDB table, you need to use the `point_in_time_recovery` block within the `aws_dynamodb_table` resource. This feature ensures that the table can be restored to any point in time within the last 35 days (up to the earliest system backup retention period).

Here is the complete Terraform configuration:

```hcl
resource "aws_dynamodb_table" "example" {
  name           = "ExampleTable"
  billing_mode   = "PAY_PER_REQUEST"
  hash_key       = "PrimaryKey"

  attribute {
    name = "PrimaryKey"
    type = "S"
  }

  # Enable Point-in-Time Recovery (PITR)
  point_in_time_recovery {
    enabled = true
  }

  tags = {
    Environment = "Production"
  }
}
```

