3.  **Create the S3 Object**: We use the `aws_s3_object` resource to upload a file.
    *   The `bucket` argument needs to reference the ID of the bucket created in the previous step. We do this using `aws_s3_bucket.example.id` to create an implicit dependency, ensuring the bucket exists before the object upload is attempted.
    *   The `source` argument is set to the local file path provided by the user: "path/to/file".
    *   The `key` argument defines the name of the file once it is inside the bucket. We will map this to the source path "path/to/file" so it retains the same structure/name inside the bucket.

