This configuration creates a VPC with public subnets, an Internet Gateway, a security group allowing PostgreSQL access, and an RDS instance.

**Note**: AWS RDS has a minimum storage requirement of 20GB for PostgreSQL instances. While the request specified 5GB, the configuration below uses 20GB to ensure the infrastructure can be successfully provisioned.

