*   `allocated_storage`: The starting size (e.g., 20 GB).
*   `max_allocated_storage`: The upper limit (e.g., 100 GB). RDS will automatically increase storage between these two values as needed.
*   `storage_type`: Set to `gp2` (or `gp3`), which supports autoscaling.

